{"author":"Iso Tester","data":{"alias":"rusty-blend-panel","description":"## Why\nThe single `state[\"signature\"]` slot is last-writer-wins, so one kind clobbers another.\nThis is the root-cause fix: an additive, kind-keyed store.\n## What\nReplace the slot with `state[\"attestations\"]`, a map keyed by attestation kind, applied\nper-key-LWW like `process_workflow_run`. `process_signature` routes by `data[\"kind\"]`\n(fallback: kind parsed from `manifest[0]`). New clones fold a legacy single `signature`\ninto the map on read so old tickets and old-clone SNAPSHOTs still work. Compaction must\nround-trip all kinds.\n## Scope\n`src/rebar/reducer/_processors.py` (`process_signature`, snapshot restore/fold-in),\n`src/rebar/schemas/ticket_state.schema.json`. No change to the signed payload.\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] `attestations` map replaces the single slot; additive across kinds, replace within a kind.\n- [ ] Routing by `data[\"kind\"]` with `manifest[0]` fallback for legacy events.\n- [ ] Legacy single `signature` folded into `attestations` on read (kind derived from its manifest).\n- [ ] Compaction/SNAPSHOT round-trips all kinds; `ticket_state` schema documents `attestations`.\n- [ ] Empty map omitted from `show`/state (no `attestations: {}` leak).","id":"114f-3eea-190e-4972","parent_id":"4702-a55c-7aeb-445a","priority":2,"tags":[],"ticket_type":"story","title":"Reducer + state model: attestations{} kind-keyed map"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1782782694963147001,"uuid":"b2d32aa1-5315-4370-a717-d701202e10f1"}